org.soulwing.snmp

Interface SnmpCompletionService<V>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BlockingQueueSnmpCompletionService

    public interface SnmpCompletionService<V>
    A service that awaits the completion of SnmpFuture instances.
    Author:
    Carl Harris

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean isIdle()
      Tests whether this completion service has a remaining event that has not yet been retrieved.
      SnmpEvent<V> poll()
      Gets an event representing a completed response if one is available.
      SnmpEvent<V> poll(long timeout)
      Gets a response event waiting as long as the specified duration for one to become available.

      • isIdle

        boolean isIdle()
        Tests whether this completion service has a remaining event that has not yet been retrieved.
        Returns:
        true if an incomplete response event remains

      • poll

        SnmpEvent<V> poll()
        Gets an event representing a completed response if one is available.
        Returns:
        completed response event or null if none is available

      • poll

        SnmpEvent<V> poll(long timeout)
                  throws InterruptedException
        Gets a response event waiting as long as the specified duration for one to become available.
        Parameters:
        timeout - timeout in milliseconds
        Returns:
        response event or null if one did not become available within the specified time interval
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - if the calling thread is interrupted while waiting

        SnmpEvent<V> take()
                  throws InterruptedException

        Returns:
        completed response
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - if the calling thread is interrupted while waiting

      • submit

        void submit(SnmpOperation<V> operation)
        Submits an operation to the service.

        The operation is invoked asynchronously and its response is placed into the queue managed by this service. service.

        Parameters:
        operation - the operation to invoke
